instructions:
  - Phase 1: Comprehensive Feature Requirements Analysis and Context Discovery
      - MANDATORY: Complete feature understanding:
          - Feature requirements analysis:
              - Parse ALL functional requirements
              - Identify ALL technical needs
              - Map ALL business objectives
              - List ALL constraints
              - Define ALL success criteria
              - Map ALL stakeholder needs
              - DOUBLE-CHECK: Nothing missed
          - System context analysis:
              - Analyze ALL existing systems
              - Map ALL integration points
              - Identify ALL dependencies
              - Document ALL constraints
              - Map ALL data flows
              - MANDATORY: Complete context
          - Domain analysis:
              - Map ALL domain entities
              - Identify ALL business rules
              - Document ALL workflows
              - Map ALL state transitions
              - Identify ALL invariants
              - FORBIDDEN: Incomplete domain model
          - Cross-cutting concerns identification:
              - Security requirements
              - Performance requirements
              - Scalability requirements
              - Reliability requirements
              - Observability requirements
              - Compliance requirements
              - MANDATORY: All concerns addressed

  - Phase 2: Feature Architecture Design with SOLID/DRY/KISS Principles
      - MANDATORY: Complete architectural design:
          - Component architecture design:
              - Design ALL feature components
              - Define ALL component interfaces
              - Plan ALL component interactions
              - Map ALL component dependencies
              - Design ALL component lifecycles
              - MANDATORY: SOLID compliance
          - SOLID principle application:
              - Single Responsibility design
              - Open/Closed design
              - Liskov Substitution design
              - Interface Segregation design
              - Dependency Inversion design
          - DRY/KISS enforcement:
              - Common pattern identification
              - Shared component design
              - Simple solution preference
              - Complexity minimization
              - Code reuse maximization
              - DOUBLE-CHECK: No duplication

  - Phase 3: Technical Specifications and API Design
      - MANDATORY: Complete technical specifications:
          - API specification design:
              - REST API design
              - GraphQL API design
              - Event API design
              - Integration patterns
              - MANDATORY: Fault tolerance
          - Data model specifications:
              - Entity design
              - Database design
              - Caching design
              - FORBIDDEN: Unvalidated data

  - Phase 4: Security and Performance Architecture
      - MANDATORY: Security architecture design:
          - Authentication design
          - Authorization design
          - Data protection design
          - Security monitoring
          - MANDATORY: Secure by default
      - Performance architecture design:
          - Scalability design
          - Performance optimization
          - MANDATORY: Meet SLAs

  - Phase 5: Integration and Deployment Architecture
      - MANDATORY: Integration architecture design:
          - External integration design
          - Internal integration design
          - Data integration design
          - MANDATORY: Fault tolerance
      - Deployment architecture design:
          - Infrastructure design
          - CI/CD pipeline design
          - FORBIDDEN: Manual deployment

  - Phase 6: Observability and Operational Architecture
      - MANDATORY: Observability design:
          - Monitoring design
          - Logging design
          - Alerting design
          - MANDATORY: Full observability
      - Operational design:
          - Maintenance design
          - Disaster recovery design
          - MANDATORY: Zero data loss

validation_criteria:
  architecture_complete: "MANDATORY - Complete feature architecture designed"
  specifications_complete: "MANDATORY - All technical specifications defined"
  solid_compliance: "MANDATORY - SOLID/DRY/KISS principles applied"
  security_by_design: "MANDATORY - Security designed from start"
  performance_designed: "MANDATORY - Performance requirements addressed"
  observability_designed: "MANDATORY - Full observability designed"
  integration_patterns: "MANDATORY - Integration patterns defined"
  production_ready: "MANDATORY - Production readiness designed"

execution_protocol: |
  MANDATORY REQUIREMENTS:
  - MUST analyze complete feature requirements
  - MUST design with SOLID/DRY/KISS principles
  - MUST address all cross-cutting concerns
  - MUST design for production readiness
  - MUST include security by design
  - MUST design for scalability
  - MUST design for observability
  - MUST define complete specifications
  - MUST design integration patterns

  STRICTLY FORBIDDEN:
  - NO implementation details
  - NO test design here
  - NO incomplete specifications
  - NO security afterthoughts
  - NO performance afterthoughts
  - NO monolithic designs
  - NO tight coupling
  - NO duplicate patterns
  - NO undocumented decisions

  ARCHITECTURE PRINCIPLES:
  - Design for change
  - Design for scale
  - Design for failure
  - Design for security
  - Design for observability
  - Design for maintainability
  - Design for reuse
  - Design for simplicity
